# ☕ Coffee Day Cafe — Backend Setup

## Folder Structure
```
your-project/
├── backend/
│   ├── server.js       ← Express backend (this file)
│   ├── package.json    ← Dependencies
│   └── db.json         ← Auto-created JSON database
├── login.html          ← Updated login page
├── new.html            ← Your cafe page (needs 1 edit — see below)
└── client.js           ← Frontend API script (replaces old server.js)
```

## Step 1 — Install Node.js
Download from https://nodejs.org (choose LTS version)

## Step 2 — Install dependencies
Open a terminal in the `backend/` folder and run:
```bash
npm install
```

## Step 3 — Update new.html (1 line change)
Find this line in new.html:
```html
<script href="server.js"></script>
```
Replace it with:
```html
<script src="../client.js"></script>
```

Also update all `addToCart()` button calls to pass the item info, e.g.:
```html
<button onclick="addToCart('cappuccino', 'Cappuccino')">Add to Cart</button>
<button onclick="addToCart('brownie', 'Brownie')">Add to Cart</button>
```

And update the reservation form's onsubmit:
```html
<form onsubmit="return validateForm()">
```

And the review form's onsubmit:
```html
<form onsubmit="return reviewAlert(event)">
```

## Step 4 — Start the server
```bash
npm start
```

## Step 5 — Open in browser
```
http://localhost:3000/login.html
```

